                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.67/3–2149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubby</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="45" xml:id="d1332fn45">Repeated to the Consul General at
                        Tientsin as telegram No. 60.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 21, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. Urtel unnumbered [<hi rend="italic">129</hi>] March 6 economic conditions
                    since Jan. 15.<note n="46" xml:id="d1332fn46">Not printed.</note> For action
                    Tientsin Shanghai, would ConGen consider feasible attempt send courier
                    commercial vessels Shanghai–Taku Bar under present conditions. Is pouch exchange
                    Taku Bar or alternate procedure possible. Dept anxious reestablish direct
                    communications. Your opinion requested necessity sending two couriers for
                    security.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
